1 - create lang folder
    php artisan lang:publish
2 - copy en folder inside lang folder and make ar or tr folder
3 - creat file user.php in all folder (en ,ar , tr) to write phrases for user in all language

user.php in ar folder

 <?php
    return [
    'direct'  => 'rtl',
    'dashboard' => "الصفحة الرئيسية" ,
    'addCourse' => "اضافة دورة دراسية" ,
    ];
 ?>

user.php in en folder

 <?php
    return [
        'direct'  => 'ltr',
        'dashboard' => "Dashboard " ,
        'addCourse' => "Add Course  " ,
    ];
 ?>

 4 - in route
    Route::get('/lang/{locale}' , function(string $locale){
        if (! in_array($locale, ['en', 'ar', 'tr'])) {
            return view('error');
        }
        session()->put('locale' , $locale);
        return redirect()->back();
    })->name('lang');

5 - in links in view pages. and change languages like (ar , tr)
    <a href="{{route('lang' ,'en')}}">

6 - create middleware
    php artisan make:middleware LangConversion

7 - add path of middleware in app->http->kernel  inside
    protected $middlewareGroups = [          // it mean that files is defined in all route
        'web' => [
            .
            .
            .
            \App\Http\Middleware\LangConversion::class,
        ],

8 - in LangConversion file in Middleware
    {
        if(session()->has('locale')){

            App::setLocale(session()->get('locale'));
        }
        return $next($request);
    }
9 - now in view pages change phrases with phrases in user file

    <p> {{ __('user.addCourse')}} </p>